caption: My sadness is that I will not be able to try all the burritos before I leave town. That crispy rice reminded me of paella, which is wonderful. For covid, they have takeout packages, or you can sit at one of the tables out front.

Very good burritos but also very expensive. Keep in mind I come from a rural area and am in the city for college, so expensive to me may be different from expensive to you. A great place for vegetarian food though

Had a chickalo burrito and the philluminati bowl (both with fajita veggies) for our first visit here. Truly delicious food! Everything was exactly what I wanted. Spicy food was spicy, creamy sauces were creamy, all of it was full of flavor. We will definitely be repeat customers!

Several weeks after eating here for the first time, we will look at each other and say "that burrito was really good..."  The food here is amazing and I would take a non-vegan here for lunch without hesitation.

This place is open. No dine in currently due to the pandemic. The quality of the food since I first started dining here has changed. The service is always friendly though. Also the menu is quite small.
